    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Display your selected post and page.<br />\nA very simple plugin to add selectable post and page &#8211; for WordPress.</p>\n<h4>Features include</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Easy to install</li>\n<li>Use for any sidebar.</li>\n<li>Get post(s) directly by a list of selected posts.</li>\n<li>Widget to display the post feature image. </li>\n<li>It will be displayed at random as the featured image of any post without an image.</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the &#8216;selectable-post-and-page&#8217; folder to the &#8216;/wp-content/plugins/&#8217; directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the &#8220;selectable-post-and-page&#8221; list plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Go to &#8216;Appearance&#8217; &gt; &#8216;Widgets&#8217; and place the widget into a sidebar to configure it.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.3.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added get image from Post.</li>\n<li>Added Post-Image class.</li>\n<li>Added Post views three layouts(Default, Full image, Title lists(no images)).</li>\n<li>Improved front-end css design.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added Random Post option.</li>\n<li>Improve some code.</li>\n<li>Added input of &#8220;More&#8221; and &#8220;Date&#8221;.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release.</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
